<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="669" type="taxonomic comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="669">Taxonomic comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="669">
The species can be diagnosed by its posteriorad or vertical orientation of the scale rows of the neck and the supra-axillary region, this separates the species from 
<taxonomicName family="Agamidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. htunwini" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="669" rank="species" species="htunwini">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="669">C. htunwini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; detailed comparisons with 
<taxonomicName family="Agamidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. versicolor" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="669" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="669">C. versicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species resurrected and elevated in this communication are provided in the diagnoses and comparisons sections of those species. The species was thought to have a narrower distribution in the Central Dry Zone of Myanmar, in comparison to 
<taxonomicName family="Agamidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. htunwini" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="669" rank="species" species="htunwini">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="669">C. htunwini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zug, G" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="669" pagination="35 - 68" refId="B69" refString="Zug, G, Brown, H, Schulte, II J, Vindum, J, 2007. Systematics of the Garden Lizards, Calotes versicolor Group (Reptilia, Squamata, Agamidae), in Myanmar: Central Dry Zone Populations. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 57 (2): 35 - 68" title="Systematics of the Garden Lizards, Calotes versicolor Group (Reptilia, Squamata, Agamidae), in Myanmar: Central Dry Zone Populations." volume="57" year="2007">Zug et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). It was subsequently reported from the northeast Indian states of Assam and Tripura (
<bibRefCitation author="Das, A" journalOrPublisher="Hamadryad" pageId="0" pageNumber="669" pagination="117 - 134" refId="B15" refString="Das, A, Saikia, U, Murthy, B, Dey, S, Dutta, K, 2009. A herpetofaunal inventory of Barail Wildlife Sanctuary and adjacent regions, Assam, north-eastern India. Hamadryad 34 (1): 117 - 134" title="A herpetofaunal inventory of Barail Wildlife Sanctuary and adjacent regions, Assam, north-eastern India." volume="34" year="2009">Das et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Anonymous" journalOrPublisher="Taprobanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="669" publicationUrl="http://www.indianreptiles.org/sp/890/Calotes-irawadi" refId="B6" refString="Anonymous, 2020. Calotes irawadi Zug, Brown, Schulte &amp; Vindum, 2006 - Irawadi Forest Lizard. In: Khandekar A, Roy P, Kunte K (Eds) Reptiles of India, v. 1.24. Indian Foundation for Butterflies. http://www.indianreptiles.org/sp/890/Calotes-irawadi" title="Calotes irawadi Zug, Brown, Schulte &amp; Vindum, 2006 - Irawadi Forest Lizard. In: Khandekar A, Roy P, Kunte K (Eds) Reptiles of India, v. 1.24. Indian Foundation for Butterflies." url="http://www.indianreptiles.org/sp/890/Calotes-irawadi" year="2020">Anonymous 2020</bibRefCitation>
), and has recently been reported from Western Yunnan, China (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/herpetozoa.34.e62596" author="Liu, S" journalOrPublisher="Herpetozoa" pageId="0" pageNumber="669" pagination="83 - 88" refId="B36" refString="Liu, S, Zuo, C, Rao, D, 2021. Distribution extension of Calotes irawadi Zug, Brown, Schulte &amp; Vindum, 2006, previously confused with C. versicolor (Daudin, 1802): first record from China. Herpetozoa 34: 83 - 88, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/herpetozoa.34.e62596" title="Distribution extension of Calotes irawadi Zug, Brown, Schulte &amp; Vindum, 2006, previously confused with C. versicolor (Daudin, 1802): first record from China." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/herpetozoa.34.e62596" volume="34" year="2021">Liu et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Our samples from northeast Indian states of Arunachal Pradesh and Tripura belonged to Clade2 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. The ML phylogenetic output representing the ML + BI phylogeny based on the 1130 bp long 16 S + COI combined dataset representing the clustering pattern of the sequences of the Calotes versicolor species complex. Values at the nodes indicate ultrafast ML bootstrap values / BI posterior probabilities. Colour code follows that of Figure 1. Calotes grandisquamis and Calotes nemoricola were used as the outgroup to root the trees." figureDoi="10.3897/vz.71.e62787.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/600929" pageId="0" pageNumber="669">2</figureCitation>
), thus confirming the occurrence of the species in northeast India.
</paragraph>
